{
  "texts": [
    "Meanwhile, limited work has been done in evaluating bias in data and feature engineering (S2).",
    "As noted by S7 (Yu et al., 2020) and S8 (Hu & Rangwala, 2020), biased data and features can contribute to the unfairness of predictive algorithms, as they may reflect historical prejudices, demographic inequalities, and cultural stereotypes.",
    "According to S2 (Sha et al., 2022), bias is inherent in most real-world education datasets.",
    "All the three datasets: Moodle dataset from Monash University, Xue-TangX KDDCUP (2015) dataset, and the Open University Learning Analytics (OULA) dataset exhibited distribution and hardness bias (Kuzilek et al., 2017).",
    "60% of forum posts in the Moodle dataset were authored by female students while over 68% of the KDDCUP dataset were male student data."
  ]
}